        "content": "**Current scope**: host-runtime pod and agent observability dashboard. This variant keeps the same compact card rhythm as the shared dashboard, but restores the lower monitor canvas with host-safe evidence. `CPU Usage / Memory Usage / Memory Working Set / Socket / network / packet / disk read-write` now come from run-scoped gauges backed by agent process-tree sampling. `CPU Load` and `filesystem capacity` remain shared host-level signals, so the host dashboard deduplicates them at `pod_ip / node_label` scope instead of repeating one line per same-machine agent. Use this view to keep old monitor density without reintroducing misleading whole-machine totals as fake per-agent series.",
